column4: I found myself getting upset by quite trivial things because the ongoing tension with my advisors and dissertation committees has made me more sensitive to small stressors.
I was aware of dryness of my mouth occasionally, likely due to feeling anxious and stressed about my academic situation.
I couldn't seem to experience any positive feeling at all as the constant negative feedback and lack of support have taken a toll on my overall mood.
I experienced breathing difficulty to some degree, especially during meetings with my advisors when discussing my dissertation progress.
I just couldn't seem to get going because the overwhelming pressure and strained relationships have dampened my motivation and drive.
I tended to over-react to situations given the heightened emotional state I find myself in due to the ongoing issues with my advisors.
I had a feeling of shakiness occasionally, particularly before important meetings or presentations related to my research.
I found it difficult to relax as the constant stress and feeling of being undervalued have kept me on edge most of the time.
I found myself in situations that made me so anxious I was most relieved when they ended, especially interactions with my advisors and committee members.
I felt that I had nothing to look forward to due to the struggles and conflict within my academic circles overshadowing any sense of future accomplishment.
